cs.DB, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.LG, cs.IR 

This paper discusses big data benchmarking and identifying dwarfs workloads in big data analytics. It involves analyzing algorithms and identifying units of computation, which are relevant to database systems (cs.DB), distributed and parallel computing (cs.DC), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), machine learning (cs.LG), and information retrieval (cs.IR).
